                            <h2 class="text-brand">Lake Morskie Oko</h2>



                            <p>
                                <strong>Morskie Oko</strong> in Slavic means the “Eye of the Sea”, it is the most
                                extensive lake and the
                                fourth one of the deepest of the <em>Tatra Mountains</em>. It has been recognized by the
                                Wall
                                Street Journal as one of the five most beautiful lakes in the world. The trail distance
                                is 7.7 km and the estimated walking time is 2 hours and 30 minutes. If you have small
                                children you can pay the horse carriage to take you up, the cost if of 50 PLN to go up
                                and 30 PLN for going down (quite expensive). The day we went it was beautiful since it
                                was sunny but the temperature was not that high around 20° Celsius. Once you arrive at
                                the lake the view is just beautiful, you can rest, eat and take a beer, or you can
                                decide to go around the lake. We decide to trail all around the lake, my kids, 10 and 6
                                have great fun going thru the trails and watching the views of the mountains and the
                                waterfalls around it.
                            </p>


                            <img class="post-img img-responsive text-center"
                                src="assets/images/bitesoftheworldmx-zakopane-morskie-min.jpeg" alt="Morskie Oko Lake"
                                title="Morskie Oko Lake">


                            <h2 class="text-brand">Krupowki Street</h2>


                            <p>
                                Krupowki Street is the heart of <strong>Zakopane</strong>. Closed to traffic, paved with
                                granite cube is
                                a place visited by every tourist staying in <strong>Zakopane</strong>. We have dinner
                                there in the
                                <a href="https://www.gazdowokuznia.pl/" title="Gazodwo Kuznia" rel="external">Gazdowo
                                    Kuznia</a>. This restaurant is located in one of the oldest buildings in
                                <strong>Zakopane</strong>
                                (1891) was the first hotel located “Pod Giewontem”. We have an excellent dinner. We
                                order Rosol, which is a broth (chicken soup) with noodles, one of my favorites soups in
                                Poland, and this one from Gazdowo was particularly good. I order for my only but my kids
                                once they try it also want one for them. I try the Pork Knuckle and my son Santiago,
                                which is 10, order the roasted duck. Everything was delicious are very well served. I
                                have a sampler of Gimberger beer, the Rouge beer surprise me positively, it is an
                                aromatic beer with palpable strawberry, cranberry, and elderberry notes.
                            </p>

                            <img class="post-img img-responsive text-center"
                                src="assets/images/bitesoftheworldmx-zakopane-rosol-min.jpeg"
                                alt="Zakopane Rosol" title="Zakopane Rosol">

                            <h2 class="text-brand">Gubalowka</h2>


                            <p>
                                The next day we went to Gubalowka mountain. From the apartment, we stay probably was a 7
                                min walk to get to the funicular that will take you up. It offers a spectacular view of
                                the Tatras and <strong>Zakopane</strong>. At the top, there are some restaurants and
                                shops but also you
                                get a chance to get into the Gravitational Slide. The slide is super fun for the kids, I
                                will say is a must when you take your kids to <strong>Zakopane</strong>.
                            </p>

